  "prompt": "Nexus 6 touch and screen replacement?",
  "response": "If you're considering a **Nexus 6** touchscreen and screen replacement, here\u2019s a guide to help you navigate the process:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Assess the Issue**\n- Determine whether the issue is with the **touch functionality**, the **display**, or both.\n- If the screen is cracked but the touch still works, you might only need a **glass replacement** (more challenging).\n- If both the screen and touch are malfunctioning, you\u2019ll need a **full screen assembly** (recommended for most users).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Purchase a Replacement Screen**\n- **Full Screen Assembly**: This includes the digitizer (touchscreen) and LCD display, pre-assembled for easier installation.\n  - Price: Approximately **$50\u2013$100** (varies by seller).\n  - Check compatibility: Ensure it\u2019s specifically for the **Nexus 6** (model: Motorola Shamu).\n- **Tools Needed**: Replacement screen, adhesive, and a repair kit (includes pry tools, screwdrivers, etc.).\n\n---\n\n### **3. DIY Replacement Steps**\n- **Watch a Tutorial**: Search for a detailed Nexus 6 screen replacement video on YouTube for step-by-step guidance.\n- **General Steps**:\n  1. Power off the device.\n  2. Use a heat gun or hairdryer to soften the adhesive around the screen edges.\n  3. Carefully pry off the screen using a plastic opening tool.\n  4. Disconnect the ribbon cables for the display and digitizer.\n  5. Remove any remaining adhesive and clean the frame.\n  6. Attach the new screen assembly and reconnect the ribbon cables.\n  7. Secure the screen with new adhesive and reassemble the phone.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Professional Repair**\n- If you\u2019re not comfortable with DIY repairs, take your Nexus 6 to a professional repair shop.\n- Cost: Typically **$100\u2013$150**, depending on the shop and location.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Tips**\n- **Backup Data**: Before starting the repair, back up all your data to avoid losing important information.\n- **Buy Quality Parts**: Opt for OEM or high-quality third-party screens to ensure durability.\n- **Be Patient**: Take your time during the repair to avoid damaging other components.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like recommendations on where to buy replacement parts or tools!",
